                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/92.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-28T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Discreetly inquire of General Carranza what his future attitude will be toward
                    the Brothers of the Christian Schools in Mexico. Department understands that all
                    these schools are now closed and orders issued for expulsion of the Brothers.
                    Ascertain if order of expulsion will be revoked and schools permitted to
                    reopen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
